If you&#x27;re following the instructions here: <a href="http://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/146849/how-do-i-recompile-bash-to-avoid-the-remote-exploit-cve-2014-6271-and-cve-2014-7" rel="nofollow">http://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/146849/how-do-i-rec...</a><p>...then this patch needs to be modified (different line numbers) before it can be applied to the Apple version of bash:<p><pre><code>    --- parse.y.old 2014-09-25 13:42:17.000000000 +0300
    +++ parse.y    2014-09-25 13:41:39.000000000 +0300
    @@ -2503,6 +2503,8 @@
       FREE (word_desc_to_read);
       word_desc_to_read = (WORD_DESC *)NULL;

    +  eol_ungetc_lookahead = 0;
    +
       last_read_token = &#x27;\n&#x27;;
       token_to_read = &#x27;\n&#x27;;
     }
</code></pre>
Testing locally, this appears to mitigate both known (so far) vulnerabilities.
